      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 96: 🔴 Critical Issues - `notePushReceived()` posts the cancellation behind any already-due `deactivateRunnable`. If the app is backgrounded and the main looper has a due deactivation queued, a background FCM call can enqueue the timestamp update after that stale runnable; the service may restore accounts, then the stale runnable deactivates them again before call negotiation completes, causing missed incoming calls. Remove the pending callback synchronously before posting the state update, then arm the delayed check from the main block. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\nfun notePushReceived(isCallPush: Boolean) {\n    val now \u003d SystemClock.elapsedRealtime()\n    backgroundHandler.removeCallbacks(deactivateRunnable)\n    backgroundHandler.post {\n        lastPushTime \u003d now\n        if (isCallPush) lastCallPushTime \u003d now\n        backgroundHandler.removeCallbacks(deactivateRunnable)\n        backgroundHandler.postDelayed(deactivateRunnable, BACKGROUND_DEACTIVATION_DELAY_MS)\n    }\n}\n```",
      "revId": "5ca2c376353b9babddaf6182e5d0298a3e2d9746",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
